Mexico Economy to Grow 3.8% This Year, Banamex Survey Shows

-- B y   J o s e   E n r i q u e   A r r i o j a
-- 
2011-10-04T21:16:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-04/mexico-economy-to-grow-3-8-this-year-banamex-survey-shows.html
Mexico ’s economy will grow 3.8
percent this year, according to the median estimate of
economists surveyed by Citigroup Inc.’s Banamex unit.  The central bank’s next movement of the benchmark interest
rate will be a reduction of 25 basis points and the next move
will come in October 2012, according to the median estimate in
the survey.  Inflation will end 2011 at 3.40 percent, according to the
survey, which was released today. The peso will trade at 12.50
against the  U.S. dollar  at the end of the year, the survey
shows.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jose Enrique Arrioja in Mexico City at 
 jarrioja@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jonathan Roeder at 
 jroeder@bloomberg.net  